\f1\b0\fs38 \cf2 Makes about 2 quarts\

\i \

\fs48 Giardiniera, pronounced \{jar din nair ah\}, is a pickled vegetable condiment.\'a0 It's delicious added to sandwiches, or salads...and also tastes great as part of an antipasto.\
You can use any combination of vegetables you desire...some great additions would be fennel, eggplant, celery, or pearl onions.\'a0 Traditional canning methods, such as hot water baths, etc, are not needed here.\'a0 The high level of acid in the brine inhibits the growth of bacteria & the layer of olive oil on top seals out air.\'a0 
\i0 \

\i\fs32 \

\i0\fs56 1 head cauliflower, cut into small florets\
1 red bell pepper, large diced\
1 yellow bell pepper, large diced\
1 bunch carrots, cut into strips, or rounds 
\fs42 \cf3 (tender, young carrots that come in bunches, with the greens still attached)
\fs72 \cf2 \

\fs56 1 medium jicama, medium diced
\i \

\i0 5-6 cloves garlic\
red pepper flakes, to taste 
\fs44 (\cf3 for more heat, slice up some jalapenos, or serrano chiles)
\fs72 \cf2 \

\fs56 several sprigs of fresh dill\
10 whole peppercorns\
2 cups white vinegar\
2 cups water\
4 tablespoons kosher salt\
olive oil\
\pard\intbl\itap1\pardeftab720\sl480\ql\qnatural
\cf2 \
